<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="font-weight: bold;">September 7-10, 2010, Grenoble, France</span><br /> <br /></span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The  31th session of the INTERNATIONAL SUMMER SCHOOL OF AUTOMATIC CONTROL in  Grenoble proposes an overview of recent problems dealing with the  distributed control and estimation of networked control systems with  application to collaborative control of multi-agent systems and sensor  network. The school is organized into several lectures given by  international experts. They will bring both theoretical and practical  backgrounds.</span> <a href="http://www.gipsa-lab.inpg.fr/summerschool/auto2010/index_en.php">Program</a></p>
